## Notes

- offset is 0-index page number, not a standard offset. Increment by ++, NOT by +=limit.

- limit defaults to 100 per page

- isTitleRequired=true

- for the given purchase order, get details (expiration date and consumption details)


| **useful date fields** |  |
| --- | --- |
| purchaseOrderNumber | keep |
| startDate | date as string 'yyyy-mm-dd' |
| expiryDate | date as string 'yyyy-mm-dd' |
| productTitles | product titles on the license  <br>  <br>**For licenses where there are multiple products on a single license, unfortunately magicbox still counts a license consumption as 1 license, they cannot break down this data by product. For this reason as of 2025 we've been limiting license to a single product per license, but a lot of old licenses have multiple products |
| totalLicenseCount | total license quantity on original purchase order (inflated by first adding free admin licenses and then a 5-10% buffer increase + 10% relative to what they actually order in zoho/netsuite. For this reason early licenses from 2023/2024 may be extremely inflated in quantity). <u><b>Ideally we should really validate this number in zoho or netsuite, but it's hard to pull this data to validate</b></u>  <br>  <br>Currently admins CAN see this number in their account. (However it may be misleading b/c of license inflation vs. what they ordered. If they have questions, we ask them to refer to the official Purchase Order) |
| licenseConsumeCount | We confirmed with Magicbox that this number represents the total number of consumed licenses on the purchase order. This is the basis for what KlettWL is billed by magicbox.  <br>  <br>Currently admins CANNOT see this number directly in their account. (Instead, they see a confusing # "Licenses Used" but this is not the correct number, this is the total pool of available licenses instead). This makes tracking license consumption confusing for admins  <br>  <br>**For licenses where there are multiple products on a single license, unfortunately magicbox still counts a license consumption as 1 license, they cannot break down this data by product. For this reason as of 2025 we've been limiting license to a single product per license  <br>  <br>Licenses are consumed when a user who has been assigned the book logs in for the first time. District admins also automatically consume the license immediately even if they don't log in |
| consumeUsers | This appears to be a list of all users who have consumed a license, however there are a lot of duplicates. This might be recording every login event?  <br>  <br>I don't necessarily need this but could be useful to see which user TYPES have consumed the licenses: how many ADMINS, TEACHERS, LEARNERS  <br>esp since admin and teacher licenses are provided complimentary, we want to assess actual <u><b>student</b></u> consumption metrics (because we provide free complimentary admin and teacher licenses, we only bill for students. We are taking a profit loss on admins and teachers)  <br>consumeUsers response overspills / is paginated so to get total count I need to page through in my program and aggregate using .reduce(). this might not be worth it.... |
